Washington, D.C., area. That has
sent people rushing to

01:16.743 --> 01:21.081 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
grocery stores, as road crews
ready their equipment.

01:21.081 --> 01:24.384 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And governors in Virginia, North
Carolina and Maryland have
declared emergencies.

01:24.384 --> 01:29.489 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GOV. LARRY HOGAN (R), Maryland:
Our focus will be on clearing
all of the main state

01:29.489 --> 01:37.230 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
highways, but a great deal will
also be demanded of local
authorities in the coming days.
They

01:37.230 --> 01:44.538 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
will almost certainly be
overwhelmed by the amount of
snow and the effects of this
storm.

01:44.538 --> 01:51.378 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It could take days, or even up
to a week, for them to dig out
all local roads.

01:51.378 --> 01:55.482 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Even before
the blizzard, the Washington,
D.C., area was crippled
overnight,

01:55.482 --> 01:59.953 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
